    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay, so if we're talking about \"proven outcomes,\" then many people would argue that market-based systems actually drive more innovation and better technology because of the competition. wouldn't it be more accurate to say that the \"right\" approach is a matter of political priority rather than some objective balance of outcomes? or are you saying there is a definitive best model that everyone should eventually agree on?",
